@page "/BlazorControls/AboutQuickGrid"
@rendermode InteractiveServer
@using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.QuickGrid

<PageTitle>Blazor Components - QuickGrid</PageTitle>

<h1>The QuickGrid Component</h1>

<p>In Blazor .NET 8, Microsoft introduced the <a href="https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/aspnet/core/blazor/components/quickgrid?view=aspnetcore-8.0" target="_blank"><code>&lt;QuickGrid&gt;</code> component</a> as <q cite="https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/aspnet/core/blazor/components/quickgrid?view=aspnetcore-8.0">a Razor component for quickly and efficiently displaying data in tabular form.</q> It's important to note that you must <b>add a package reference to <code>Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.QuickGrid</code></b> and include the appropriate <code>@@using</code> statement in your Razor page in order to use QuickGrid. <i>Click the accordian titles below to view each demo.</i></p>

<article>
    <details>
        <summary role="button" class="secondary"><b>Promotion Grid</b> Adaptation</summary>
        <h2>Promotion Grid Example</h2>

        <QuickGrid Items="@people">
            <PropertyColumn Property="@(p => p.PersonId)" Sortable="true" />
            <PropertyColumn Property="@(p => p.Name)" Sortable="true" />
            <PropertyColumn Property="@(p => p.PromotionDate)" Format="yyyy-MM-dd" Sortable="true" />
        </QuickGrid>

        @code {
            private record Person(int PersonId, string Name, DateOnly PromotionDate);

            private IQueryable<Person> people = new[]
            {
                new Person(10895, "Jean Martin", new DateOnly(1985, 3, 16)),
                new Person(10944, "António Langa", new DateOnly(1991, 12, 1)),
                new Person(11203, "Julie Smith", new DateOnly(1958, 10, 10)),
                new Person(11205, "Nur Sari", new DateOnly(1922, 4, 27)),
                new Person(11898, "Jose Hernandez", new DateOnly(2011, 5, 3)),
                new Person(12130, "Kenji Sato", new DateOnly(2004, 1, 9)),
            }.AsQueryable();
        }
    </details>
</article>
